Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 System Overview			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Project Offline is an offline desktop project management application for Microsoft Windows. It provides Microsoft Project Pro compatible functionality built with Python, PyQt5 and MPXJ. The application requires no internet access, cloud services, or subscription.	information	1.1	PO-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Purpose			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The purpose of this document is to define the software requirements for Project Offline v1.x.	information	1.1.1	PO-INFO-002.0	Not relevant		
1.2 Scope			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system scope covers task scheduling, resource management, Gantt charting, team planning, baseline tracking, timeline visualisation, and optional enterprise integrations (KeePass, Confluence Calendar).	information	1.2.1	PO-INFO-003.0	Not relevant		
2 General Requirements			2	2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall run entirely offline without requiring internet access or cloud services.	functional requirement	2.1	PO-GEN-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall be a native desktop application targeting Microsoft Windows 10 and later.	functional requirement	2.2	PO-GEN-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall be implemented in Python 3.9 or later using the PyQt5 GUI framework.	functional requirement	2.3	PO-GEN-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall use the MPXJ library (via JPype) to read and write Microsoft Project files.	functional requirement	2.4	PO-GEN-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall present a Microsoft Project Pro look-and-feel with an Office blue ribbon, toolbar, and menu bar using Segoe UI fonts.	functional requirement	2.5	PO-GEN-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall support keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+N (new), Ctrl+O (open), Ctrl+S (save), Insert (add row), Delete (delete row), Ctrl++ / Ctrl+- (zoom), Ctrl+Z (undo), Ctrl+Y (redo).	functional requirement	2.6	PO-GEN-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall be distributable as a standalone Windows executable that bundles Python, OpenJDK 17, MPXJ, and all Python dependencies with no additional installation required.	functional requirement	2.7	PO-GEN-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
3 Application Startup and Shutdown			3	3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
3.1 General Startup Behaviour			3.1	3_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	On first launch with no project open, the application shall disable all task and resource editing actions until a project file is created or opened.	functional requirement	3.1.1	PO-GEN-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The application shall accept a --open <path> command-line argument to open a project file directly at startup.	functional requirement	3.1.2	PO-GEN-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On application exit, the system shall prompt the user to save unsaved changes.	functional requirement	3.1.3	PO-GEN-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
3.2 External Tool Bootstrapping			3.2	3_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	When system Java is not available, the launcher shall provision a bundled OpenJDK for Windows distribution into tools/java.	functional requirement	3.2.1	PO-GEN-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When system Git is not available, the launcher shall provision a bundled Git for Windows distribution into tools/git.	functional requirement	3.2.2	PO-GEN-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When system SVN is not available and TortoiseSVN is installed, the launcher shall copy required SVN command-line binaries into tools/svn.	functional requirement	3.2.3	PO-GEN-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
3.3 Bundled-First Tool Resolution			3.3	3_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	At application startup, the runtime shall prefer a bundled OpenJDK over system Java; if no bundled JDK is found, system Java (JAVA_HOME / PATH) shall be used as fallback.	functional requirement	3.3.1	PO-GEN-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	At application startup, the runtime shall prefer a bundled Git over system git.exe; if no bundled git.exe is found, system Git shall be used as fallback.	functional requirement	3.3.2	PO-GEN-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	At application startup, the runtime shall prefer a bundled SVN over system svn.exe; if no bundled svn.exe is found, system SVN shall be used as fallback.	functional requirement	3.3.3	PO-GEN-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
4 Ribbon UI Behaviour			4	4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
4.1 Split-Button Dropdowns			4.1	4_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Split-buttons in the ribbon that provide multiple related actions shall display their dropdown as a rich listview popup (bold action title + optional subtitle line) instead of a plain QMenu, to improve discoverability and provide context for each action.	functional requirement	4.1.1	PO-GEN-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When a ribbon listview popup is open and the user clicks a ribbon tab or activates any other ribbon button, the popup shall close automatically without requiring an additional click to dismiss it.	functional requirement	4.1.2	PO-GEN-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
